cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the generalization ability of deep neural networks (DNNs) and their classification ability. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on the optimization process and the combination of classifiers. The paper also discusses the activation patterns of hidden nodes, which suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper's focus on classification and the use of fully-connected feedforward networks suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's discussion of classification accuracy and consistency suggests a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
